31/10/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska President Dragan Cavic called on the People's Assembly Thursday (30 October) to adopt the defence reform bill drafted by the line federal commission. 
Cavic said the document is a pre-requisite for BiH's entry into the Partnership for Peace programme and that the country may incur losses from further delay.
In Sarajevo, the BiH government adopted an action plan for border security and the fight against organised crime Thursday. 
The document recommends legal amendments, reform of police structures, witness protection and a set of new regulations against money laundering. 
(SRNA - 30/10/03)
